Iskul Bukol ran on Philippine television for ten highly successful years from 1978 to 1987. The first of the one hour and a half sitcoms, it chronicled the ups and downs of college life in the fictional Wanbol University, where storylines ran chiefly around the doings of campus hooligans in the persons of half-siblings Tito (Tito Sotto) and Joey Escalera (Joey de Leon) that make probinsiyano Victorio Ungasis (Vic Sotto) miserable.
